dismissalText.commentary: Aiden Markram b Holder 9 (34b 1x4 0x6 57m) SR: 26.47

dismissalComment.html: Holder's first ball has off stump cartwheelng. 125ks, on a length, landed around fourth and seamed back in. Markram, a touch unlucky, as that skidded without much bounce. He wanted to defend with a straight bat and off the back foot, which was the bigger issue given the indications from this pitch so far. Big gap between bat and pad breached. Holder doing a high-knee dance in celebration.

dismissalText.commentary: Tony de Zorzi c Hodge b Warrican 78 (145b 7x4 2x6 207m) SR: 53.79

dismissalComment.html: a soft, soft dismissal. It was full around off and de Zorzi went for the fine reverse sweep. But Warrican bowled this slightly slower, resulting in the batter gloving it to the slip. Hodge at slip had started to move to his left but reacted quickly when he saw the ball coming to his right

dismissalText.commentary: Tristan Stubbs c Holder b Roach 20 (48b 2x4 0x6 69m) SR: 41.66

dismissalComment.html: The slips being close pays off, Holder goes low to the left, swings his palms across and snaffles it. Length, the key, for Roach, along with the wide-of-crease release. Pushed it up at around the fuller side of length, angled it in towards fifth stump. Stubbs needn't have played at that but was dragged by the release angle. He wanted to push to cover by the looks of it. First slip, behind Holder, dove across too but the latter got early and used his reach well. He yells in delight

dismissalText.commentary: Temba Bavuma lbw b Seales 86 (182b 7x4 1x6 265m) SR: 47.25

dismissalComment.html: Full toss gets Bavuma, he was ready to walk but Verreynne convinces him to review. This was out though, the new ball looked to be going leg side but swung towards off. Beat the flick and hit around shin-height. Bavuma was almost out the ground by the time Hawk-Eye showed it'd go on to hit off stump. Seales deserved a wicket that over. Bavuma's 89 vs NZ in 2017 remains his highest away score in an innings

dismissalText.commentary: David Bedingham c Carty b Seales 29 (45b 3x4 1x6 60m) SR: 64.44

dismissalComment.html: The leg-side trap works, Seales has broken through! There is a third-umpire check but Bedingham's halfway back. dismissalText.commentary: David Bedingham c Carty b Seales 29 (45b 3x4 1x6 60m) SR: 64.44

dismissalComment.html: The leg-side trap works, Seales has broken through! There is a third-umpire check but Bedingham's halfway back. Carty, at deep forward square leg, was a few metres in from the boundary and diving forward, he scooped it with cupped wrists just above the grass. Zoomed picture is blurry but the fingers seem underneath even as they scrape the grass, and he wrings them upon falling chest-first into the ground. Holds onto it while tumbling and the third umpire is happy. Was a shortish 127ks ball around off that rose to around rib-height. Bedingham went with the old-school pull, with the front leg cranking up, and he didn't want to keep it down but failed to hit the gap. First home Test wicket for Seales

And this is a no-ball as well - Ngidi had overstepped - but that doesn't affect the run-out

dismissalText.commentary: Kraigg Brathwaite run out (Mulder) 35 (131b 2x4 1x6 337m) SR: 26.71

dismissalComment.html: a direct hit at the bowler's end. And we are going upstairs. It was a full ball around off that Brathwaite flicked to the right of mid-on and set off.
